      "rationale": "Primary QOI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) in g/100 L, which is the direct clinical metric used for VAD hemolysis acceptance. Secondary QOIs include scalar shear stress (SSS) and exposure time distributions, which are mechanistically linked to the hemolysis model. QOIs are identical between validation experiments and COU predictions.",
